                    <div xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xml:lang="en" type="original">
<pb f="1r" n="1" xml:id="pb-orig-1r-1" facs="#zone-pb-1r-1"/>

<p xml:id="p.en.1" n="1"><hi rend="italics">St Jerome’s love.</hi><ptr target="#note-t-1"/></p>
<space unit="lines" quantity="1"/>

<p xml:id="p.en.2" n="2">Who is the maid my spirit seeks</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.3" n="3">Through cold reproof, and slanders blight –</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.4" n="4">Has she loves roses on her cheeks?</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.5" n="5">Is her’s an eye of calm delight?</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.6" n="6">No – wan and sunk with midnight prayer</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.7" n="7">Are the pale looks of her I love</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.8" n="8">And if by times a light be there</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.9" n="9">That light is kindled from above.–</p>
<space unit="lines" quantity="1"/>

<p xml:id="p.en.10" n="10">I choose not her mine hearts elect</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.11" n="11">’Mongst those that seek their Makers shrine</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.12" n="12">In gems and garlands proudly decked</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.13" n="13">As if themselves were things divine.–</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.14" n="14">No, heaven but faintly warms the breast</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.15" n="15">That beats beneath a broidered veil.</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.16" n="16">And she, who comes in glittering dress</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.17" n="17">To mourn her frailty – yet is frail.–</p>
<space unit="lines" quantity="1"/>

<p xml:id="p.en.18" n="18">Not so the faded form I prize</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.19" n="19">And love because her bloom is gone</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.20" n="20">The glory of those sainted eyes</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.21" n="21">Is all the dress her brow puts on.–</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.22" n="22">But ne’er was beauties bloom so bright,</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.23" n="23">So touching as that forms decay</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.24" n="24">Which as the altars wavering light</p>

<p xml:id="p.en.25" n="25">In holy lustre fades away.–</p>
<space unit="lines" quantity="1"/>

<p xml:id="p.en.26" n="26">Harriet Beecher Stowe.</p>
<space unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
